00114 Ctrl_status at45dbx_usb_read_10(U32 addr, U16 nb_sector)
00115 {
00116   if (addr + nb_sector > AT45DBX_MEM_CNT << (AT45DBX_MEM_SIZE - AT45DBX_SECTOR_BITS)) return CTRL_FAIL;
00117 
00118   at45dbx_read_open(addr);
00119   at45dbx_read_multiple_sector(nb_sector);
00120   at45dbx_read_close();
00121 
00122   return CTRL_GOOD;
00123 }
00124 
00125 
00126 void at45dbx_read_multiple_sector_callback(const void *psector)
00127 {
00128   U16 data_to_transfer = AT45DBX_SECTOR_SIZE;
00129 
00130   // Transfer read sector to the USB interface.
00131   while (data_to_transfer)
00132   {
00133     while (!Is_usb_in_ready(g_scsi_ep_ms_in));
00134 
00135     Usb_reset_endpoint_fifo_access(g_scsi_ep_ms_in);
00136     data_to_transfer = usb_write_ep_txpacket(g_scsi_ep_ms_in, psector,
00137                                              data_to_transfer, &psector);
00138     Usb_ack_in_ready_send(g_scsi_ep_ms_in);
00139   }
00140 }
00141 
00142 
00143 Ctrl_status at45dbx_usb_write_10(U32 addr, U16 nb_sector)
00144 {
00145   if (addr + nb_sector > AT45DBX_MEM_CNT << (AT45DBX_MEM_SIZE - AT45DBX_SECTOR_BITS)) return CTRL_FAIL;
00146 
00147 #if AT45DBX_MEM_TEST_CHANGE_STATE == ENABLED
00148   if (nb_sector) s_b_data_modify = TRUE;
00149 #endif
00150 
00151   at45dbx_write_open(addr);
00152   at45dbx_write_multiple_sector(nb_sector);
00153   at45dbx_write_close();
00154 
00155   return CTRL_GOOD;
00156 }
00157 
00158 
00159 void at45dbx_write_multiple_sector_callback(void *psector)
00160 {
00161   U16 data_to_transfer = AT45DBX_SECTOR_SIZE;
00162 
00163   // Transfer sector to write from the USB interface.
00164   while (data_to_transfer)
00165   {
00166     while (!Is_usb_out_received(g_scsi_ep_ms_out));
00167 
00168     Usb_reset_endpoint_fifo_access(g_scsi_ep_ms_out);
00169     data_to_transfer = usb_read_ep_rxpacket(g_scsi_ep_ms_out, psector,
00170                                             data_to_transfer, &psector);
00171     Usb_ack_out_received_free(g_scsi_ep_ms_out);
00172   }
00173 }
